      <processinfo id="aspace_74f0fab0156559a6c466713850e5712d">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_9f49d91171c3a73ad2f3729d8e7dbb97">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of student records maintained by the Yale School of Drama.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_3530cb2b0d426ee93adc3126e65b7c92">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records for the classes of 1928-1982 are arranged alphabetically. Subsequent classes are arranged by class year.</p>  
      </arrangement>
  
